### =============================================================================
### health.http — RESQID Super Admin · Health Monitor
### =============================================================================
### Setup:
###   1. Install REST Client extension (Huachao Mao) in VS Code
###   2. Run login request first → copy token → set @token below
###   3. Or use the JS pre-request script in your .env file
###
### Variables — fill these before running
### =============================================================================

@baseUrl    = http://localhost:3000
@token      = PASTE_YOUR_SUPER_ADMIN_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
@incidentId = inc-PASTE_AFTER_CREATING


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 0. LOGIN  (run this first to get your token)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [0] Super Admin Login
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/super-admin
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@resqid.in",
  "password": "your-password-here"
}

###
# After login succeeds:
#   1. Copy the accessToken from the response
#   2. Paste it into @token above
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. FULL SYSTEM HEALTH
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [1] Get full health snapshot
# What the frontend Refresh button calls.
# Returns: overall_status, services[], incidents[], dlq_unresolved, stalled_pipelines
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. SERVICE STATUSES
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [2] Get service statuses only (lighter endpoint)
# Returns: overall_status + services[] without incident data
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/services
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 3. INCIDENTS — LIST
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [3a] List all incidents (default — no filters)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [3b] List active incidents only (excludes RESOLVED)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents?active_only=true
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [3c] Filter by status — INVESTIGATING
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents?status=INVESTIGATING
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [3d] Filter by status — IDENTIFIED
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents?status=IDENTIFIED
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [3e] Filter by status — MONITORING
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents?status=MONITORING
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [3f] Filter by status — RESOLVED
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents?status=RESOLVED
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 4. INCIDENTS — CREATE
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [4a] Create incident — HIGH severity (SMS Gateway)
# Copy the returned `id` → set @incidentId above
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "SMS Gateway elevated latency",
  "severity": "HIGH",
  "affected_services": ["sms", "notif"],
  "message": "Outbound SMS delivery is experiencing elevated latency above 1200ms. Vendor notified and investigating."
}

###

### [4b] Create incident — MEDIUM severity (single service)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Email service degraded performance",
  "severity": "MEDIUM",
  "affected_services": ["email"],
  "message": "Email delivery success rate has dropped to 85%. Provider support ticket raised."
}

###

### [4c] Create incident — LOW severity (scheduled maintenance)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Scheduled DB maintenance window",
  "severity": "LOW",
  "affected_services": ["db"],
  "message": "Planned maintenance on Neon Postgres cluster. Expected downtime: 5 minutes. Scheduled for 02:00 IST."
}

###

### [4d] Create incident — CRITICAL (full outage)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Complete API server outage",
  "severity": "CRITICAL",
  "affected_services": ["api", "db", "redis", "qr", "notif"],
  "message": "API server is not responding. All services are affected. Team is actively investigating."
}

###


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 5. INCIDENTS — GET SINGLE
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [5a] Get incident by ID (set @incidentId after creating)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents/{{incidentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### [5b] Get non-existent incident (expect 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents/inc-doesnotexist
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 6. INCIDENTS — UPDATE (PATCH)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [6a] Update status → IDENTIFIED
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents/{{incidentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "IDENTIFIED",
  "message": "Root cause identified: MSG91 rate limiting on our API key due to spike in OTP requests. Contacted vendor to raise limits."
}

###

### [6b] Update status → MONITORING (with escalated severity)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents/{{incidentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "MONITORING",
  "severity": "HIGH",
  "message": "Fix applied. Monitoring delivery rates for the next 30 minutes before marking resolved."
}

###

### [6c] Resolve incident
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents/{{incidentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "RESOLVED",
  "message": "Delivery rates returned to normal. Incident resolved. Post-mortem scheduled for Monday."
}

###

### [6d] Update message only (no status change)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents/{{incidentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "Engineering team is actively working on the fix. ETA: 20 minutes."
}

###

### [6e] Update severity only
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents/{{incidentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "severity": "CRITICAL"
}

###


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 7. VALIDATION ERROR CASES  (all should return 422)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [7a] Create — missing required fields
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Incomplete incident"
}

###

### [7b] Create — title too short
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Hi",
  "severity": "LOW",
  "affected_services": ["api"],
  "message": "Some message that is long enough to pass"
}

###

### [7c] Create — invalid service ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Test with bad service",
  "severity": "LOW",
  "affected_services": ["invalid-service"],
  "message": "This should fail validation on affected_services"
}

###

### [7d] Create — invalid severity
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Test with bad severity",
  "severity": "SUPER_HIGH",
  "affected_services": ["api"],
  "message": "This should fail on severity validation"
}

###

### [7e] Update — empty body (expect 422 — at least one field required)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents/{{incidentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### [7f] List — invalid status filter (expect 422)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health/incidents?status=UNKNOWN_STATUS
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###


# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 8. AUTH ERROR CASES
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### [8a] No token (expect 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health

###

### [8b] Malformed token (expect 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health
Authorization: Bearer this.is.not.a.valid.jwt

###

### [8c] Wrong role — school admin token (expect 403)
# Replace with a valid SCHOOL_ADMIN token to test RBAC
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/super-admin/health
Authorization: Bearer PASTE_SCHOOL_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE

###
